#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn55.31"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn55.31:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 55 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 55 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.31:0.2"
msgid "4. Puññābhisandavagga "
msgstr "4. Overflowing Merit "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 31. Paṭhamapuññābhisandasutta → abhisandasuttaṃ (bj) | abhisanda 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.31:0.3"
msgid "31. Paṭhamapuññābhisandasutta "
msgstr "31. Overflowing Merit (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.391, sc1
msgctxt "sn55.31:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.31:1.2"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puññābhisandā kusalābhisandā sukhassāhārā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of overflowing merit, overflowing goodness that nurture happiness. "

msgctxt "sn55.31:1.3"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn55.31:1.4"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—"
msgstr "Firstly, a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha … "

msgctxt "sn55.31:1.5"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.31:1.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ paṭhamo puññābhisando kusalābhisando sukhassāhāro. "
msgstr "This is the first kind of overflowing merit, overflowing goodness that nurtures happiness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn55.31:2.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—"
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the teaching … "

msgctxt "sn55.31:2.2"
msgid "svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo … pe … paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhīti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.31:2.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ dutiyo puññābhisando kusalābhisando sukhassāhāro. "
msgstr "This is the second kind of overflowing merit, overflowing goodness that nurtures happiness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn55.31:3.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako saṅghe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—"
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Saṅgha … "

msgctxt "sn55.31:3.2"
msgid "suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.31:3.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ tatiyo puññābhisando kusalābhisando sukhassāhāro. "
msgstr "This is the third kind of overflowing merit, overflowing goodness that nurtures happiness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn55.31:4.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple’s ethical conduct is loved by the noble ones, unbroken, impeccable, spotless, and unmarred, liberating, praised by sensible people, not mistaken, and leading to immersion. "

msgctxt "sn55.31:4.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ catuttho puññābhisando kusalābhisando sukhassāhāro. "
msgstr "This is the fourth kind of overflowing merit, overflowing goodness that nurtures happiness. "

msgctxt "sn55.31:4.3"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puññābhisandā kusalābhisandā sukhassāhārā”ti. "
msgstr "These are the four kinds of overflowing merit, overflowing goodness that nurture happiness.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn55.31:4.4"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

